result.execSummary:
The defendant Lonnie R. Nylund was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Lonnie R. Nylund is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Lonnie R. Nylund was found guilty of Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Lonnie R. Nylund was found guilty of Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).
  • Lonnie R. Nylund was found guilty of Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

09:45 am - Defendant Lonnie R. Nylund in court with attorney Michael John Rielly.  Steven Mitchell Michlig appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty of counts 2 and 3 but defers judgment on Count 1 and accepts the DPA.  Michlig/Rielly/Court statement to sentencing.    The court informs defendant of right to request expungement of the DNA under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4).
